steps.instruction:
### Chicken
- Place the chicken in a large pot, add the water and cover.
- Bring to a boil under high heat
- Once boil has been reached reduce to medium-low
- Let simmer for about 10 minutes or chicken is lo longer pink
- Shred chicken with forks and set shredded chicken aside. 

### Soup Sauce
- In a medium saucepan combine cream of chicken soup, sour creme and chili powder
- Bring to a simmer under low heat, stirring occasionally, then turn off heat and cover to keep warm

### Filling
- Heat butter in skillet over medium heat.
- Stir in onion; cook and stir until the onion has softened and turns translucent (about 5 minutes)
- Add shredded chicken, chopped green chilies, taco seasoning, half the bunch of green onions, and water and simmer for 10 minutes

### Everything in the pan
- Preheat the oven for 350F
- Stir in 1 cup of the soup mixture into the chicken mixture. 
- Spread the remaining soup mixture on the bottom of a 9x13 inch baking dish
- Fill each tortilla with chicken mixture
- Sprinkle cheese over the chicken filling before folding the tortillas seam side down in the pan
- Pour the enchilada sauce evenly over the enchiladas.
- Cover with the remaining 1.5 cups of cheddar cheese.
- Sprinkle the reserved chopped green onions and sliced olives on top of the cheese.
- Bake in the preheated oven until the filling is heating and the cheese is melted and bubbling (about 25 minutes)
